The Japan Foundation Center for Cultural Exchange in Vietnam proudly presents Japanese Film Festival 2015: Colors of Love from 9 October – 14 November 2015 in Ho Chi Minh City, Danang and Hanoi.

Japanese Film Festival is one of the most anticipated annual events of the Japan Foundation and it is widely known that its free tickets are quickly ran out in few days, thanks to the enthusiastic Japanese film fans in Vietnam.

This year’s film festival focuses on the introduction of Japanese films under the theme of “Shape of Heart”. We will screen Six Japanese films, which portray various shapes of hearts, loves among friends, families, lovers. The festival’s opener is “Beyond the Memories” (2013/dir. SHINJO Takehiko).  

All films will be screened with both English and Vietnamese sub-titles. The admission is free, but audience is advised to obtain free tickets at following venues.

Film Festival Information:

[Film list: (please click on the film titles for their synopsis)]

♥ My Pretend Girlfriend
(2014/dir. YAKUMO Saiji)
♥ Beyond the Memories	
(2013/dir. SHINJO Takehiko)
♥ It All Began When I Met You	
(2013/dir. MOTOKI Katsuhide)
